<paragraph id="8BF236A7FFF3FFE226C431C7FEB0FC78" blockId="22.[151,741,886,948]" box="[151,329,922,948]" pageId="22" pageNumber="263">
(
<figureCitation id="13762A22FFF3FFE226CC31C7FEF1FC78" box="[159,264,922,948]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1842,1866]" captionTargetBox="[189,1390,494,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-152@23.[189,1398,489,1818]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 8. Iassinae and Hylicinae. A–H, Tardrabassus pakneunensis Dai &amp; Dietrich, female: A–B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, face and anterior part of thorax, ventral view; D, sternite VII, ventral view (left side damaged); E, gonoplacs; F–G, first valvula; H, second valvula. I–O, Traiguma hamocauda sp. n., holotype male: I–J, lateral and dorsal habitus; K–J, genital capsule, lateral ventral views; M, pygofer, ventral view; N, subgenital plates, ventral view; O–P, genitalia, ventral and lateral views; Q, aedeagus, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4424108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4424108/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="263">Figures 8</figureCitation>
A–H)
</paragraph>
